1
00:01:37,009 --> 00:01:40,160
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,190 --> 00:01:43,060
[Episode 22]

3
00:01:43,450 --> 00:01:44,900
No matter what others think of you

4
00:01:44,900 --> 00:01:46,360
or what the outcome may be,

5
00:01:46,370 --> 00:01:47,640
speak up about

6
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:48,420
your expectations

7
00:01:48,420 --> 00:01:49,750
when you want them most.

8
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:02,690
What are you doing?

9
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:03,870
What are you doing?

10
00:02:03,870 --> 00:02:04,590
You bumped into me,

11
00:02:04,590 --> 00:02:06,650
and now you're asking what I'm doing?

12
00:02:08,210 --> 00:02:09,669
We really have no rapport.

13
00:02:11,030 --> 00:02:11,860
Yunfei, you're here?

14
00:02:11,860 --> 00:02:12,260
Hurry.

15
00:02:12,270 --> 00:02:13,020
Come on in.

16
00:02:13,340 --> 00:02:14,250
No, thanks.

17
00:02:14,280 --> 00:02:15,460
I was walking your sister home.

18
00:02:15,460 --> 00:02:16,300
Now that she's home, I'm leaving.

19
00:02:16,300 --> 00:02:16,880
Stay a bit.

20
00:02:16,880 --> 00:02:17,650
No, really.

21
00:02:17,680 --> 00:02:18,590
I have a deadline.

22
00:02:18,590 --> 00:02:19,920
I won't see you out then.

23
00:02:20,680 --> 00:02:21,400
Bye.

24
00:02:26,320 --> 00:02:27,980
You were pretty forward, huh?

25
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:29,579
Come on.

26
00:02:32,700 --> 00:02:34,360
How is your shop coming along?

27
00:02:35,350 --> 00:02:36,750
We're painting the walls.

28
00:02:36,750 --> 00:02:37,710
Nima and Yan are helping me.

29
00:02:37,710 --> 00:02:38,440
Almost done.

30
00:02:40,960 --> 00:02:42,560
It's going pretty smoothly?

31
00:02:44,829 --> 00:02:45,770
In what sense?

32
00:02:46,970 --> 00:02:47,970
What do you think?

33
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:51,230
Yan...

34
00:02:51,630 --> 00:02:52,400
agreed

35
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,380
to give it a try with me.

36
00:02:54,430 --> 00:02:55,630
Who asked about that?

37
00:02:55,730 --> 00:02:57,660
I was asking about the renovation.

38
00:02:58,530 --> 00:02:59,340
I really should have

39
00:02:59,340 --> 00:03:00,210
taken a picture

40
00:03:00,610 --> 00:03:01,760
of you just now.

41
00:03:03,090 --> 00:03:03,860
Even with a lame leg,

42
00:03:03,860 --> 00:03:04,650
you didn't...

43
00:03:04,650 --> 00:03:05,510
Hold me steady.

44
00:03:06,070 --> 00:03:07,070
You talk too much.

45
00:03:07,340 --> 00:03:08,250
You took the initiative

46
00:03:08,250 --> 00:03:08,960
to kiss him.

47
00:03:08,980 --> 00:03:10,130
Say that again and I'll slap you.

48
00:03:10,130 --> 00:03:10,900
And you actually stood on your tiptoes

49
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:11,580
to kiss him.

50
00:03:11,600 --> 00:03:12,260
Stop it!

51
00:03:14,230 --> 00:03:14,830
Mom.

52
00:03:15,030 --> 00:03:16,230
What are you writing?

53
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:18,329
A self-criticism.

54
00:03:40,750 --> 00:03:41,500
You're done?

55
00:03:42,180 --> 00:03:43,380
Is it serious enough?

56
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:44,970
Very.

57
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,360
Should I read it to you?

58
00:03:46,360 --> 00:03:46,860
Okay.

59
00:03:46,940 --> 00:03:48,070
I'll sign it for you.

60
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:49,620
Mom.

61
00:03:51,960 --> 00:03:52,970
Let me give you a massage.

62
00:03:52,970 --> 00:03:53,840
No, don't.

63
00:03:53,910 --> 00:03:54,579
I won't survive

64
00:03:54,579 --> 00:03:55,460
your massage.

65
00:03:55,630 --> 00:03:56,650
I've learned it.

66
00:03:57,070 --> 00:03:58,400
It's good for your legs.

67
00:03:59,060 --> 00:03:59,840
I used to massage your dad's legs

68
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,220
just like this.

69
00:04:01,250 --> 00:04:03,050
I don't deserve such treatment.

70
00:04:03,590 --> 00:04:04,360
Mom.

71
00:04:04,910 --> 00:04:06,120
You're being so gentle all of a sudden.

72
00:04:06,120 --> 00:04:07,210
It's scary.

73
00:04:08,540 --> 00:04:09,910
You're not afraid of the Uninhabited Zone,

74
00:04:09,910 --> 00:04:11,240
but you're afraid of me?

75
00:04:12,530 --> 00:04:12,870
Here.

76
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:14,690
I'll be gentle.

77
00:04:21,240 --> 00:04:22,450
Listen.

78
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:25,810
Since you started mountain patrolling,

79
00:04:25,810 --> 00:04:28,270
how many times
have you gone to the hospital?

80
00:04:28,940 --> 00:04:29,940
Look at your face.

81
00:04:30,260 --> 00:04:32,190
It's almost rougher than my hands.

82
00:04:35,550 --> 00:04:36,520
Do you have to

83
00:04:36,580 --> 00:04:38,490
go this far in your work?

84
00:04:39,450 --> 00:04:40,710
Didn't you always say

85
00:04:40,740 --> 00:04:41,250
women should have

86
00:04:41,250 --> 00:04:42,310
their own careers?

87
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,920
You were alone before,

88
00:04:45,170 --> 00:04:46,470
but now you have Shao.

89
00:04:47,440 --> 00:04:49,120
If you have a family in the future,

90
00:04:49,120 --> 00:04:49,750
are you going to keep

91
00:04:49,750 --> 00:04:51,360
running off like this?

92
00:04:52,450 --> 00:04:53,240
Why are you talking about

93
00:04:53,240 --> 00:04:54,920
having a family?

94
00:04:55,740 --> 00:04:56,370
We haven't gotten

95
00:04:56,370 --> 00:04:57,870
to that stage yet.

96
00:04:58,550 --> 00:04:59,570
But you'll get there

97
00:04:59,570 --> 00:05:00,700
sooner or later.

98
00:05:01,600 --> 00:05:03,220
And you need to consider

99
00:05:03,350 --> 00:05:05,610
where you're going to start this family.

100
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:08,300
Shao isn't forcing you

101
00:05:08,300 --> 00:05:09,950
to make a decision right now.

102
00:05:10,720 --> 00:05:11,860
He's accommodating you,

103
00:05:11,860 --> 00:05:13,060
But that doesn't mean

104
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,870
he can wait forever.

105
00:05:18,160 --> 00:05:18,760
Mom.

106
00:05:19,690 --> 00:05:20,920
Do you think

107
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,390
I should go to the provincial capital?

108
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:24,820
Whether a marriage is happy

109
00:05:24,820 --> 00:05:26,680
doesn't depend on where you live.

110
00:05:27,050 --> 00:05:29,510
There are divorces in provincial capitals,

111
00:05:29,510 --> 00:05:30,190
and lifelong loving couples

112
00:05:30,190 --> 00:05:31,880
in the counties.

113
00:05:33,120 --> 00:05:34,120
The key is

114
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:36,070
whether you two will

115
00:05:36,110 --> 00:05:37,770
never get tired of each other.

116
00:05:39,300 --> 00:05:42,030
If you don't want
to go to the provincial capital,

117
00:05:42,060 --> 00:05:43,200
maybe

118
00:05:43,920 --> 00:05:45,920
Shao is willing to accommodate you.

119
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:50,490
You mean...

120
00:05:51,390 --> 00:05:53,100
asking him to move here?

121
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,260
Would he be willing to do that?

122
00:05:57,630 --> 00:05:58,860
Shao Yunfei

123
00:05:59,480 --> 00:06:00,370
is ambitious

124
00:06:00,390 --> 00:06:01,590
and has his own ideas.

125
00:06:03,060 --> 00:06:03,930
Even if he stays here

126
00:06:03,930 --> 00:06:04,920
because of me,

127
00:06:06,310 --> 00:06:07,920
can our county satisfy him?

128
00:06:08,440 --> 00:06:09,760
That's not the point.

129
00:06:10,250 --> 00:06:11,450
The point is

130
00:06:11,780 --> 00:06:13,460
you must believe in yourself.

131
00:06:15,750 --> 00:06:16,680
Believe in what?

132
00:06:17,620 --> 00:06:20,020
Believe that you are worthy
of being loved.

133
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,260
Believe in your choices.

134
00:06:24,350 --> 00:06:25,220
Believe that

135
00:06:25,560 --> 00:06:26,960
even if you miss this one,

136
00:06:27,310 --> 00:06:28,370
it doesn't matter.

137
00:06:28,980 --> 00:06:31,540
Don't compromise yourself.

138
00:06:38,850 --> 00:06:40,250
Mom, do you believe in me?

139
00:06:42,040 --> 00:06:43,600
If I didn't believe in you,

140
00:06:43,630 --> 00:06:46,690
I wouldn't have agreed
to let you go into the mountains.

141
00:06:58,920 --> 00:06:59,450
Captain.

142
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,760
What's the situation?

143
00:07:02,030 --> 00:07:03,400
We found this on the truck.

144
00:07:03,400 --> 00:07:05,280
It's much shorter than sheep wool—

145
00:07:05,280 --> 00:07:07,280
definitely Tibetan antelope wool.

146
00:07:07,790 --> 00:07:08,520
Poaching,

147
00:07:09,180 --> 00:07:09,930
illegal gold mining,

148
00:07:09,930 --> 00:07:11,130
unlawful detention—

149
00:07:12,310 --> 00:07:12,980
I wonder what else

150
00:07:12,980 --> 00:07:14,310
these people have done.

151
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:16,310
The trucks all have reinforced

152
00:07:16,310 --> 00:07:17,440
steel suspensions.

153
00:07:18,000 --> 00:07:19,460
They load cargo every time
without overloading.

154
00:07:19,460 --> 00:07:20,830
It must be preparation

155
00:07:20,860 --> 00:07:21,920
for unpaved roads.

156
00:07:22,010 --> 00:07:22,870
Most suspiciously,

157
00:07:22,870 --> 00:07:23,470
every week

158
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,100
2 trucks leave at midnight

159
00:07:25,190 --> 00:07:27,070
carrying gasoline, timber,

160
00:07:27,140 --> 00:07:27,880
and flour.

161
00:07:29,810 --> 00:07:31,320
Transporting timber
to the Uninhabited Zone?

162
00:07:31,320 --> 00:07:32,720
Very suspicious indeed.

163
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:34,740
He.

164
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,250
What about your end?

165
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:37,100
We once tailed

166
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:38,480
a logistics company truck

167
00:07:38,480 --> 00:07:40,150
all the way into the Uninhabited Zone,

168
00:07:40,150 --> 00:07:41,750
but we didn't bring supplies

169
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:43,220
and didn't know how long

170
00:07:43,250 --> 00:07:44,020
or how far we'd have to go,

171
00:07:44,020 --> 00:07:45,330
so we stopped following.

172
00:07:45,330 --> 00:07:46,480
How much grain and fuel do

173
00:07:46,480 --> 00:07:47,630
they transport each time?

174
00:07:47,630 --> 00:07:49,560
We couldn't get into their office,

175
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:50,659
so we couldn't find

176
00:07:50,659 --> 00:07:52,060
the detailed manifests.

177
00:07:52,770 --> 00:07:53,720
These are figures estimated

178
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,830
by visual inspection.

179
00:07:54,830 --> 00:07:55,500
Take a look.

180
00:07:58,350 --> 00:07:59,120
That much?

181
00:08:00,540 --> 00:08:02,130
At two jin of rations per person

182
00:08:02,130 --> 00:08:02,810
per day,

183
00:08:03,230 --> 00:08:04,870
there have to be
at least 100 people inside.

184
00:08:04,870 --> 00:08:05,330
However,

185
00:08:05,330 --> 00:08:06,770
they cover their tracks well.

186
00:08:06,770 --> 00:08:08,010
They never transport weapons

187
00:08:08,010 --> 00:08:09,570
or ammunition on this route,

188
00:08:09,570 --> 00:08:10,120
so

189
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:11,660
we can't tell

190
00:08:11,680 --> 00:08:13,250
how many guns they actually have.

191
00:08:13,250 --> 00:08:14,210
Should we report this

192
00:08:14,210 --> 00:08:15,300
to the police

193
00:08:15,390 --> 00:08:16,450
and ask for backup?

194
00:08:16,590 --> 00:08:17,540
The police

195
00:08:18,070 --> 00:08:18,830
don't have experience operating

196
00:08:18,830 --> 00:08:20,230
in the Uninhabited Zone.

197
00:08:20,490 --> 00:08:21,580
If they go in rashly

198
00:08:21,740 --> 00:08:23,070
and alert those people,

199
00:08:23,590 --> 00:08:25,420
they'll scatter and run away like pikas.

200
00:08:25,420 --> 00:08:26,740
Why don't we just

201
00:08:26,770 --> 00:08:27,880
set up a roadblock on the highway,

202
00:08:27,880 --> 00:08:28,850
stop their trucks,

203
00:08:28,850 --> 00:08:30,080
and ask them?

204
00:08:31,500 --> 00:08:32,429
On what grounds?

205
00:08:32,809 --> 00:08:33,460
Grain and fuel

206
00:08:33,460 --> 00:08:34,169
aren't contraband.

207
00:08:34,169 --> 00:08:35,210
Just beat them up.

208
00:08:35,390 --> 00:08:37,010
I bet we can make them talk.

209
00:08:37,549 --> 00:08:38,880
Don't bring Bai with us.

210
00:08:41,770 --> 00:08:42,700
Forget I said it.

211
00:08:45,310 --> 00:08:46,340
Once the support funding and equipment

212
00:08:46,340 --> 00:08:47,460
are in place,

213
00:08:48,170 --> 00:08:49,880
we'll follow them in ourselves first,

214
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:50,510
figure out

215
00:08:50,530 --> 00:08:52,420
the gold mining sites and headcount,

216
00:08:52,420 --> 00:08:54,650
and then report
to the county and the police.

217
00:08:54,650 --> 00:08:55,200
He,

218
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,460
get the supplies
for going into the mountains

219
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:56,890
ready.

220
00:08:56,940 --> 00:08:57,940
For how many days?

221
00:08:58,050 --> 00:08:59,450
Prepare for the maximum.

222
00:08:59,540 --> 00:09:01,470
Bring all the guns and ammunition.

223
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,530
If things turn violent,

224
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,940
we can't be at a disadvantage.

225
00:09:20,390 --> 00:09:21,630
Why did you come back with two vehicles?

226
00:09:21,630 --> 00:09:22,740
The county didn't allocate the funds.

227
00:09:22,740 --> 00:09:23,770
County Mayor Lin said

228
00:09:23,770 --> 00:09:25,200
he'd give us an extra vehicle instead.

229
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:26,030
What about the guns and ammo?

230
00:09:26,030 --> 00:09:26,750
In the back.

231
00:09:33,140 --> 00:09:34,020
That's it?

232
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:35,590
It's way too little.

233
00:09:35,820 --> 00:09:37,460
Weren't we promised support?

234
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:39,060
What kind of support is this?

235
00:09:39,970 --> 00:09:40,970
They gave us a car.

236
00:09:42,620 --> 00:09:43,480
Chief Shi said

237
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:45,080
the report has been submitted.

238
00:09:45,080 --> 00:09:45,580
The semi-automatic rifles

239
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:46,450
and 7.62mm ammunition

240
00:09:46,450 --> 00:09:48,170
won't arrive
until next month at the earliest.

241
00:09:48,170 --> 00:09:49,310
This is the maximum support

242
00:09:49,310 --> 00:09:50,780
he can offer for now.

243
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:20,550
Captain.

244
00:10:25,030 --> 00:10:26,250
How many months' salaries

245
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,510
are we behind on?

246
00:10:30,370 --> 00:10:31,440
Four months.

247
00:10:35,560 --> 00:10:36,210
Make it up.

248
00:10:39,950 --> 00:10:41,150
There's no other way.

249
00:10:43,730 --> 00:10:45,330
We can only use the dead sheep

250
00:10:45,970 --> 00:10:47,300
to save the living ones.

251
00:11:05,940 --> 00:11:06,290
Mom,

252
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:08,200
the girl I met last time

253
00:11:08,200 --> 00:11:09,130
was really nice,

254
00:11:09,200 --> 00:11:09,910
but it seems

255
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:11,470
she's not interested in me.

256
00:11:20,990 --> 00:11:21,680
Yes.

257
00:11:22,580 --> 00:11:23,590
The results are out.

258
00:11:23,590 --> 00:11:24,590
I got first place.

259
00:11:26,130 --> 00:11:27,290
What's so nice about her?

260
00:11:27,290 --> 00:11:29,350
I still didn't make the cutoff score.

261
00:11:29,620 --> 00:11:30,490
There's nothing I can do.

262
00:11:30,490 --> 00:11:31,820
I'll just take it again.

263
00:11:38,430 --> 00:11:40,120
Mom, stop crying.

264
00:11:40,670 --> 00:11:41,550
I can barely hear

265
00:11:41,550 --> 00:11:42,680
what you're saying.

266
00:11:43,190 --> 00:11:45,190
You cry every time we talk.

267
00:11:46,310 --> 00:11:47,640
I know I'm

268
00:11:47,660 --> 00:11:49,160
your only son.

269
00:11:49,450 --> 00:11:50,500
Worst case,

270
00:11:50,520 --> 00:11:52,320
you can always have another one.

271
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:06,530
Come here.

272
00:12:06,990 --> 00:12:07,670
Let me measure you

273
00:12:07,670 --> 00:12:08,900
for a new Tibetan robe.

274
00:12:08,900 --> 00:12:09,760
I don't need it.

275
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:10,870
I have clothes to wear.

276
00:12:10,870 --> 00:12:11,740
You do?

277
00:12:13,370 --> 00:12:14,000
It's been years

278
00:12:14,000 --> 00:12:15,900
since I made you a new Tibetan robe.

279
00:12:15,900 --> 00:12:17,470
We have to make one this year.

280
00:12:17,470 --> 00:12:18,800
That old one is worn out.

281
00:12:19,890 --> 00:12:20,270
I hardly

282
00:12:20,270 --> 00:12:21,580
wear that one anyway.

283
00:12:22,250 --> 00:12:23,650
Why spend the money on it?

284
00:12:23,770 --> 00:12:24,480
We still haven't paid back the money

285
00:12:24,480 --> 00:12:25,710
we owe Basang's family.

286
00:12:25,710 --> 00:12:27,160
Don't worry about that.

287
00:12:27,460 --> 00:12:29,590
I'll make sure it's paid off this year.

288
00:12:30,550 --> 00:12:31,170
Fine.

289
00:12:31,270 --> 00:12:33,390
You handle the household finances now,

290
00:12:33,390 --> 00:12:34,990
so we'll go with what you say.

291
00:12:35,890 --> 00:12:36,950
No need to measure.

292
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:37,820
Just take the old one

293
00:12:37,820 --> 00:12:39,100
and use it for size.

294
00:12:41,250 --> 00:12:42,070
Do you know how much weight

295
00:12:42,070 --> 00:12:43,930
you've lost in the last two years?

296
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:47,640
My wife

297
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,460
is not only more capable than me,

298
00:12:49,460 --> 00:12:50,790
but also more generous.

299
00:12:51,290 --> 00:12:52,340
I'm generous?

300
00:12:53,720 --> 00:12:54,260
One year,

301
00:12:54,290 --> 00:12:56,370
when you came back
from a meeting in Tianduo,

302
00:12:56,370 --> 00:12:57,050
you bought me

303
00:12:57,050 --> 00:12:58,710
a pair of turquoise earrings,

304
00:12:58,960 --> 00:12:59,930
saying the thing you fear least

305
00:12:59,930 --> 00:13:01,060
was spending money.

306
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:02,250
Weren't we

307
00:13:02,340 --> 00:13:03,650
dating back then?

308
00:13:09,770 --> 00:13:10,910
I told Tashi

309
00:13:11,400 --> 00:13:13,010
that his dad is very generous,

310
00:13:13,010 --> 00:13:14,410
but he didn't believe me.

311
00:13:14,460 --> 00:13:14,820
He said,

312
00:13:14,820 --> 00:13:16,580
"If Dad is really that generous,

313
00:13:16,580 --> 00:13:17,670
I want him to take us

314
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:18,580
on a trip."

315
00:13:19,190 --> 00:13:20,520
Where does he want to go?

316
00:13:20,580 --> 00:13:21,240
Gansu.

317
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:24,250
I thought

318
00:13:24,270 --> 00:13:25,730
he wanted to go to Beijing.

319
00:13:26,510 --> 00:13:28,750
He said
when he gets into college in Beijing,

320
00:13:28,750 --> 00:13:30,950
he'll have plenty of time to explore it.

321
00:13:31,030 --> 00:13:31,830
But right now,

322
00:13:31,860 --> 00:13:33,980
he wants to go to Gansu the most.

323
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:36,420
He wants to visit Yang's hometown.

324
00:13:40,360 --> 00:13:41,490
A couple of days ago,

325
00:13:42,050 --> 00:13:43,220
I took Mom to

326
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:44,150
see Director Zhang

327
00:13:44,150 --> 00:13:45,200
for a checkup.

328
00:13:46,150 --> 00:13:47,530
And I also bought you some

329
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:48,590
stomach medicine.

330
00:13:48,840 --> 00:13:49,840
When you go into the mountains this time,

331
00:13:49,840 --> 00:13:51,270
don't forget to take it with you.

332
00:13:51,270 --> 00:13:52,530
What's wrong with Mom?

333
00:13:52,590 --> 00:13:53,590
Same as always.

334
00:13:54,700 --> 00:13:55,030
Her rheumatism

335
00:13:55,030 --> 00:13:56,530
has been acting up lately.

336
00:13:58,120 --> 00:13:59,720
I'll go see her when I'm free.

337
00:14:00,100 --> 00:14:01,270
I don't have time today.

338
00:14:01,270 --> 00:14:02,320
I have to get back to the team.

339
00:14:02,320 --> 00:14:02,750
Okay.

340
00:14:04,650 --> 00:14:06,380
I've already chopped up the lamb.

341
00:14:06,380 --> 00:14:07,470
Cook it tomorrow.

342
00:14:07,790 --> 00:14:08,240
Okay.

343
00:14:08,740 --> 00:14:09,270
And earlier this afternoon,

344
00:14:09,270 --> 00:14:10,760
I patched up the hole in the tent

345
00:14:10,760 --> 00:14:11,860
that the cow poked.

346
00:14:12,770 --> 00:14:13,860
Next time you milk the cow,

347
00:14:13,860 --> 00:14:14,460
be careful

348
00:14:14,500 --> 00:14:15,700
and tie it up tightly.

349
00:14:16,050 --> 00:14:16,550
I'm off.

350
00:14:20,550 --> 00:14:21,770
Ride slowly.

351
00:14:22,220 --> 00:14:22,690
You are

352
00:14:22,720 --> 00:14:24,010
not a child anymore.

353
00:14:26,530 --> 00:14:27,860
What are you laughing at?

354
00:14:27,860 --> 00:14:28,750
Last time you said

355
00:14:28,750 --> 00:14:29,940
I was a child.

356
00:14:38,460 --> 00:14:39,460
Thank you.

357
00:14:41,800 --> 00:14:43,260
When I come back this time,

358
00:14:43,960 --> 00:14:45,090
let's go travel

359
00:14:45,110 --> 00:14:45,850
to Gansu.

360
00:14:46,420 --> 00:14:47,420
Let's relax a bit.

361
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:54,200
I almost forgot.

362
00:14:55,050 --> 00:14:56,910
You're in charge of the money now.

363
00:14:57,120 --> 00:14:58,320
I need your approval.

364
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,580
Come back soon.

365
00:15:06,630 --> 00:15:07,240
Bye!

366
00:15:07,890 --> 00:15:08,880
Ride slowly!

367
00:15:08,910 --> 00:15:09,940
Be careful on the road!

368
00:15:09,940 --> 00:15:10,440
Okay!

369
00:15:10,530 --> 00:15:10,980
Hyah!

370
00:15:11,950 --> 00:15:12,380
Hyah!

371
00:15:24,250 --> 00:15:29,830
♪ We gather here today ♪

372
00:15:30,130 --> 00:15:38,980
♪ I hope we will never be apart ♪

373
00:15:39,830 --> 00:15:42,090
♪ People who love each other ♪

374
00:15:42,500 --> 00:15:49,170
♪ I wish you eternal good health ♪

375
00:15:49,510 --> 00:15:50,460
Here comes the meat.

376
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:51,590
The mutton is ready.

377
00:15:53,080 --> 00:15:54,210
Here comes the meat!

378
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:55,910
Here comes the mutton!

379
00:15:56,170 --> 00:15:56,940
Time to eat!

380
00:16:01,290 --> 00:16:01,750
Come on!

381
00:16:01,910 --> 00:16:03,110
Let's raise our cups!

382
00:16:04,510 --> 00:16:05,550
Thanks to Captain

383
00:16:05,650 --> 00:16:06,620
for the mutton,

384
00:16:07,530 --> 00:16:08,200
and thanks to

385
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:09,730
Reporter Shao for the wine.

386
00:16:12,080 --> 00:16:12,810
Tashi Delek!

387
00:16:12,960 --> 00:16:13,690
Tashi Delek!

388
00:16:14,200 --> 00:16:15,170
Tashi Delek!

389
00:16:15,270 --> 00:16:16,360
Tashi Delek!

390
00:16:21,410 --> 00:16:21,910
Come on.

391
00:16:21,940 --> 00:16:23,200
Let's divide the meat.

392
00:16:25,530 --> 00:16:26,790
Let's divide the meat.

393
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:28,980
Shao.

394
00:16:29,510 --> 00:16:30,910
This wine is pretty good.

395
00:16:31,170 --> 00:16:32,430
This wine is so strong.

396
00:16:33,630 --> 00:16:34,410
Thank you.

397
00:16:34,900 --> 00:16:36,300
Captain is thanking you.

398
00:16:38,200 --> 00:16:39,330
He's saying thanks.

399
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:40,410
Thanks.

400
00:16:40,900 --> 00:16:41,850
Meat is here.

401
00:16:42,020 --> 00:16:42,950
You're welcome.

402
00:16:43,110 --> 00:16:43,940
Knife, knife.

403
00:16:55,080 --> 00:16:56,460
Do you know how to cut meat?

404
00:16:56,460 --> 00:16:57,350
Why are you so clumsy?

405
00:16:57,350 --> 00:16:58,060
Here, let me teach you.

406
00:16:58,060 --> 00:16:58,710
No, no, no.

407
00:16:59,170 --> 00:16:59,820
I'm a local.

408
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,550
How could I not know how to cut meat?

409
00:17:00,550 --> 00:17:01,680
Why is this knife...

410
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,240
not working well?

411
00:17:03,780 --> 00:17:05,900
A bad workman always blames his tools.

412
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:06,300
Give it to me.

413
00:17:06,300 --> 00:17:06,829
You do it.

414
00:17:07,460 --> 00:17:08,190
Give it to me.

415
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,020
Watch this.

416
00:17:12,480 --> 00:17:13,400
I saw that.

417
00:17:13,480 --> 00:17:14,050
So?

418
00:17:15,780 --> 00:17:17,510
I told you it doesn't work well.

419
00:17:17,770 --> 00:17:19,280
It really doesn't.

420
00:17:19,579 --> 00:17:20,010
Here.

421
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:21,420
Use mine.

422
00:17:27,740 --> 00:17:28,680
See?

423
00:17:28,850 --> 00:17:30,030
It was the knife's fault.

424
00:17:30,030 --> 00:17:30,850
This knife works well.

425
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:31,240
Yes.

426
00:17:31,330 --> 00:17:32,060
Give it to me.

427
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:34,570
Why do you want everything?

428
00:17:34,570 --> 00:17:35,550
That's Captain's knife.

429
00:17:35,550 --> 00:17:37,080
It's none of your business.

430
00:17:39,190 --> 00:17:40,990
This knife of mine killed a bear.

431
00:17:47,750 --> 00:17:48,340
Really?

432
00:17:52,810 --> 00:17:54,290
Since I was a teenager,

433
00:17:54,310 --> 00:17:56,310
I've been hunting in the mountains.

434
00:17:56,680 --> 00:17:58,210
I killed many wild animals—

435
00:18:01,470 --> 00:18:03,920
Tibetan foxes, blue sheep, argali,

436
00:18:04,990 --> 00:18:06,320
and white-lipped deer.

437
00:18:07,530 --> 00:18:07,910
Once,

438
00:18:07,940 --> 00:18:09,270
I even killed 3 bears.

439
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:11,650
One of them

440
00:18:13,390 --> 00:18:15,450
was stabbed to death with this knife.

441
00:18:19,470 --> 00:18:20,070
Back then,

442
00:18:20,070 --> 00:18:21,600
hunting wasn't forbidden.

443
00:18:22,340 --> 00:18:23,840
I even thought I was a hero.

444
00:18:26,900 --> 00:18:28,080
What I'm doing now

445
00:18:29,040 --> 00:18:30,770
is my way of atoning for my sins.

446
00:18:44,830 --> 00:18:46,430
Do you still want this knife?

447
00:18:48,530 --> 00:18:49,770
I don’t dare want it anymore.

448
00:18:49,770 --> 00:18:50,200
Take it back.

449
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:50,730
I want it.

450
00:18:51,050 --> 00:18:51,580
I want it.

451
00:18:52,770 --> 00:18:53,810
Why do you want everything?

452
00:18:53,810 --> 00:18:54,700
That's Captain's knife.

453
00:18:54,700 --> 00:18:55,920
It's so meaningful.

454
00:18:56,250 --> 00:18:57,710
A knife that killed a bear.

455
00:18:58,290 --> 00:18:58,810
Give it back to Captain.

456
00:18:58,810 --> 00:18:59,310
No, no.

457
00:18:59,330 --> 00:19:00,000
Wait. Let me...

458
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:00,570
Let me cut the meat first.

459
00:19:00,570 --> 00:19:02,290
Let me finish eating the meat first.

460
00:19:02,290 --> 00:19:03,460
Give it back to Captain later.

461
00:19:03,460 --> 00:19:04,060
We'll see.

462
00:19:05,070 --> 00:19:05,500
Here.

463
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:08,160
No, no.

464
00:19:08,230 --> 00:19:08,660
Here.

465
00:19:08,940 --> 00:19:09,620
Like this.

466
00:19:10,810 --> 00:19:11,570
How is it?

467
00:19:12,700 --> 00:19:13,360
How is what?

468
00:19:13,730 --> 00:19:14,930
The letter was sent,

469
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:15,960
and then?

470
00:19:17,580 --> 00:19:18,510
I didn't send it.

471
00:19:22,450 --> 00:19:23,910
Didn't you say you sent it?

472
00:19:27,180 --> 00:19:28,770
Yes, I wanted to send it.

473
00:19:29,010 --> 00:19:30,080
But I didn't.

474
00:19:31,250 --> 00:19:32,010
Why?

475
00:19:32,720 --> 00:19:34,400
Because I thought it through.

476
00:19:35,110 --> 00:19:36,240
Even if I had sent it,

477
00:19:36,330 --> 00:19:37,240
I wouldn't have known

478
00:19:37,240 --> 00:19:38,030
how we would have gotten along

479
00:19:38,030 --> 00:19:39,030
afterward.

480
00:19:42,210 --> 00:19:43,730
Every time I go into the mountains,
I stay there for so long.

481
00:19:43,730 --> 00:19:45,190
Why should she wait for me?

482
00:19:45,570 --> 00:19:46,930
I just can't give her

483
00:19:47,350 --> 00:19:48,380
a stable life.

484
00:19:49,580 --> 00:19:50,480
I can't even give her

485
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:51,260
a promise.

486
00:19:53,950 --> 00:19:54,350
Isn't...

487
00:19:54,350 --> 00:19:55,680
Isn't this your theory?

488
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:03,430
Yes.

489
00:20:03,540 --> 00:20:05,300
I did say things like that.

490
00:20:05,540 --> 00:20:06,560
But Shao Yunfei

491
00:20:06,590 --> 00:20:07,640
criticized me.

492
00:20:08,700 --> 00:20:09,200
Back then,

493
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:10,730
I had never even been in a relationship.

494
00:20:10,730 --> 00:20:12,460
Why did you have to listen to me?

495
00:20:12,830 --> 00:20:13,610
I just felt

496
00:20:13,630 --> 00:20:14,660
what you said made sense.

497
00:20:14,660 --> 00:20:15,900
So I took it to heart.

498
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,000
Yeah, it makes sense.

499
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:17,420
Exactly.

500
00:20:17,420 --> 00:20:18,280
No, it doesn't.

501
00:20:21,050 --> 00:20:22,270
I did say your situation isn't ideal

502
00:20:22,270 --> 00:20:23,970
and that there were lots of issues.

503
00:20:23,970 --> 00:20:24,600
But

504
00:20:25,030 --> 00:20:25,960
what relationship

505
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:27,290
doesn't face problems?

506
00:20:27,810 --> 00:20:29,290
Some are about location,

507
00:20:29,700 --> 00:20:31,110
and some about money.

508
00:20:31,850 --> 00:20:33,160
Finding a perfect match

509
00:20:33,160 --> 00:20:35,020
is as rare as hitting the jackpot.

510
00:20:35,460 --> 00:20:37,300
If you stop at every hurdle,

511
00:20:37,830 --> 00:20:38,400
you'll really

512
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:39,700
stay single forever.

513
00:20:41,140 --> 00:20:42,390
Shao Yunfei, what do you think?

514
00:20:42,390 --> 00:20:43,920
Are these really problems?

515
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:48,480
I guess so.

516
00:20:49,070 --> 00:20:50,070
Wrong answer.

517
00:20:50,630 --> 00:20:51,310
Try again.

518
00:20:52,180 --> 00:20:52,710
No.

519
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:53,680
Not problems.

520
00:20:53,680 --> 00:20:55,250
They're definitely not problems.

521
00:20:55,250 --> 00:20:56,270
See?

522
00:20:56,290 --> 00:20:56,590
See?

523
00:20:56,620 --> 00:20:57,050
Not a problem, right?

524
00:20:57,050 --> 00:20:57,680
See?

525
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,180
Tibetans' love

526
00:21:00,750 --> 00:21:01,520
is simpler

527
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:02,510
than you think.

528
00:21:05,250 --> 00:21:07,010
We don't care about diplomas

529
00:21:07,120 --> 00:21:08,600
or bride prices.

530
00:21:09,750 --> 00:21:12,150
As long as two people
truly love each other,

531
00:21:12,490 --> 00:21:13,950
everyone will bless them.

532
00:21:16,830 --> 00:21:17,550
Sangba,

533
00:21:18,010 --> 00:21:18,940
you've changed.

534
00:21:22,680 --> 00:21:23,250
He.

535
00:21:24,660 --> 00:21:26,190
You need to show the courage

536
00:21:26,610 --> 00:21:27,620
your Tibetan dad had

537
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:28,880
when he was pursuing your Han mom

538
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:29,490
back then.

539
00:21:30,250 --> 00:21:30,940
Be brave.

540
00:21:32,340 --> 00:21:32,890
Okay.

541
00:21:34,800 --> 00:21:35,490
Duo,

542
00:21:36,060 --> 00:21:37,610
don't dodge your responsibility.

543
00:21:37,610 --> 00:21:39,500
Now that you're not
running the development company anymore,

544
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:40,400
once the nature reserve

545
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:41,330
is established,

546
00:21:41,330 --> 00:21:42,460
you should at least

547
00:21:42,940 --> 00:21:43,750
help them secure

548
00:21:43,750 --> 00:21:45,280
a few permanent positions.

549
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:49,250
Sure.

550
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,820
I'll fight for it with the county.

551
00:21:53,480 --> 00:21:54,940
Once the reserve is set up,

552
00:21:55,360 --> 00:21:56,430
you'll be

553
00:21:56,590 --> 00:21:57,760
the first batch of rangers.

554
00:21:57,760 --> 00:21:58,560
That's right.

555
00:21:59,220 --> 00:22:00,530
There will be bread,

556
00:22:00,640 --> 00:22:01,370
and there will be permanent positions.

557
00:22:01,370 --> 00:22:02,300
Come on! Cheers!

558
00:22:02,500 --> 00:22:03,140
Here!

559
00:22:04,970 --> 00:22:05,470
Cheers!

560
00:22:07,460 --> 00:22:08,660
The noodles are here!

561
00:22:45,620 --> 00:22:48,230
[Fortress Besieged]

562
00:24:09,320 --> 00:24:10,360
Duojie said

563
00:24:10,460 --> 00:24:11,650
Sangba has changed.

564
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:14,560
Actually, I've changed too.

565
00:24:16,140 --> 00:24:16,740
Nothing

566
00:24:16,770 --> 00:24:18,140
stays the same forever.

567
00:24:19,570 --> 00:24:20,330
I used to have

568
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:21,910
no real goals

569
00:24:22,830 --> 00:24:23,680
and just wanted

570
00:24:23,680 --> 00:24:25,210
to be a good police officer.

571
00:24:26,830 --> 00:24:27,630
But somewhere

572
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:29,660
along the way,

573
00:24:31,160 --> 00:24:32,050
I started imagining

574
00:24:32,050 --> 00:24:34,310
what Bolamula's future could look like.

575
00:24:35,850 --> 00:24:36,850
It'll be a place

576
00:24:36,880 --> 00:24:37,900
with no more killing

577
00:24:37,900 --> 00:24:40,690
♪ The wind slips
through the tip of the grass ♪

578
00:24:38,760 --> 00:24:40,340
and no more destruction.

579
00:24:40,710 --> 00:24:42,710
♪ The galaxy is bright forever ♪

580
00:24:42,070 --> 00:24:43,440
Gunpowder in barrels

581
00:24:42,740 --> 00:24:44,740
♪ Silent for thousands of miles ♪

582
00:24:43,660 --> 00:24:45,110
will turn into iris seeds.

583
00:24:44,860 --> 00:24:46,610
♪ Shining over the wasteland ♪

584
00:24:46,510 --> 00:24:48,090
Permafrost torn open by tire tracks

585
00:24:46,670 --> 00:24:49,470
♪ The wind is strong
and the clothes are worn out ♪

586
00:24:48,580 --> 00:24:49,950
will sprout plum blossoms.

587
00:24:49,490 --> 00:24:50,870
♪ The wilderness stretches endlessly ♪

588
00:24:50,890 --> 00:24:52,890
♪ Our blood never gets cold ♪

589
00:24:51,550 --> 00:24:53,090
Brown bears waking from hibernation

590
00:24:52,920 --> 00:24:55,570
♪ Our spines are like mountains ♪

591
00:24:53,900 --> 00:24:55,500
will dig into sunlit slopes.

592
00:24:55,780 --> 00:24:59,200
♪ Life plants its roots ♪

593
00:24:56,810 --> 00:24:57,960
Newborn marmots

594
00:24:58,920 --> 00:25:00,500
will roll into little balls of golden fur.

595
00:24:59,220 --> 00:25:04,880
♪ In every second ♪

596
00:25:02,550 --> 00:25:04,950
And tens of thousands of Tibetan antelopes

597
00:25:05,230 --> 00:25:07,700
♪ The wind blows through the grass ♪

598
00:25:05,770 --> 00:25:07,900
will be running free

599
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:13,450
♪ And branches emerge from the earth ♪

600
00:25:08,270 --> 00:25:09,720
across endless meadows,

601
00:25:11,500 --> 00:25:13,160
just like their ancestors did

602
00:25:13,710 --> 00:25:15,180
millions of years ago.

603
00:25:17,440 --> 00:25:18,180
I know

604
00:25:19,620 --> 00:25:21,270
this future won't be easy.

605
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:23,920
But all of us

606
00:25:24,440 --> 00:25:26,170
are ready to take the first step

607
00:25:27,400 --> 00:25:28,710
toward it.

608
00:25:32,980 --> 00:25:37,430
♪ The wind blows ♪

609
00:25:38,250 --> 00:25:41,810
♪ It blows into my heart ♪

610
00:25:42,220 --> 00:25:44,480
♪ A bridge of life ♪

611
00:25:44,500 --> 00:25:49,930
♪ Rises on the horizon ♪

612
00:25:50,140 --> 00:25:54,280
♪ Flowers overflow the riverbed ♪

613
00:25:55,110 --> 00:25:59,160
♪ Covering our faces ♪

614
00:25:55,610 --> 00:25:56,570
Wangmu!

615
00:25:57,200 --> 00:25:58,270
Wangmu!

616
00:25:59,810 --> 00:26:00,540
He Qingyuan!

617
00:26:00,760 --> 00:26:05,510
♪ Turn around and look from afar ♪

618
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:02,480
I'm leaving.

619
00:26:05,750 --> 00:26:07,080
Wait for me to come back!

620
00:26:09,230 --> 00:26:13,860
♪ The wind blows ♪

621
00:26:09,800 --> 00:26:11,260
Come back early!

622
00:26:14,140 --> 00:26:17,680
♪ It blows into my heart ♪

623
00:26:17,970 --> 00:26:22,040
♪ Every speck of dust is engraved ♪

624
00:26:22,070 --> 00:26:25,820
♪ With the face you love deeply ♪

625
00:26:26,090 --> 00:26:30,600
♪ The treetops sway gently in the wind ♪

626
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:36,060
♪ Lush with leaves and branches ♪

627
00:26:31,980 --> 00:26:32,840
Watch the road.

628
00:26:36,660 --> 00:26:41,180
♪ There are hidden things in the world ♪

629
00:26:43,110 --> 00:26:48,870
♪ And time knows ♪

630
00:26:54,010 --> 00:26:54,740
That's them.

631
00:26:58,590 --> 00:26:59,390
Get in the car.

632
00:28:07,860 --> 00:28:08,990
They just passed by.

633
00:28:09,790 --> 00:28:10,340
We're too close.

634
00:28:10,340 --> 00:28:11,350
Let's wait a bit before chasing.

635
00:28:11,350 --> 00:28:11,810
Okay.

636
00:28:13,900 --> 00:28:15,280
Let's rest here for five minutes.

637
00:28:15,280 --> 00:28:15,870
Okay!

638
00:28:16,130 --> 00:28:16,690
Okay.

639
00:28:18,540 --> 00:28:20,670
If we're following just by tire tracks

640
00:28:20,830 --> 00:28:21,590
from this far back,

641
00:28:21,590 --> 00:28:22,720
what if we lose them?

642
00:28:23,350 --> 00:28:24,410
There's no choice.

643
00:28:24,440 --> 00:28:25,570
This is the only way.

644
00:28:26,050 --> 00:28:26,660
Look.

645
00:28:27,090 --> 00:28:28,550
You can see them for miles.

646
00:28:33,460 --> 00:28:34,210
What's wrong?

647
00:28:34,210 --> 00:28:35,410
Is your back hurting?

648
00:28:36,350 --> 00:28:37,610
It's too comfortable.

649
00:28:38,030 --> 00:28:39,030
I'm not used to it.

650
00:28:40,470 --> 00:28:41,200
When you get back,

651
00:28:41,200 --> 00:28:42,700
thank your mother for me.

652
00:28:43,420 --> 00:28:43,960
When we get back,

653
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:44,680
I'll find a tailor

654
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,750
and have a few more made

655
00:28:45,750 --> 00:28:47,030
so everyone can have one.

656
00:28:47,030 --> 00:28:48,630
That'll cost a lot, won't it?

657
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:50,730
You only care about money.

658
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:52,020
Don't make one for me.

659
00:28:52,020 --> 00:28:52,880
I don't want it.

660
00:28:53,830 --> 00:28:55,230
You're not paying for it.

661
00:29:15,380 --> 00:29:16,310
What's going on?

662
00:29:16,510 --> 00:29:16,920
Lack of oxygen.

663
00:29:16,920 --> 00:29:17,440
Engine stalled.

664
00:29:17,440 --> 00:29:18,140
It can't get the power up.

665
00:29:18,140 --> 00:29:18,520
Come on.

666
00:29:18,520 --> 00:29:19,320
Give me a hand.

667
00:29:19,460 --> 00:29:19,920
Okay!

668
00:29:21,240 --> 00:29:21,820
Come on!

669
00:29:22,000 --> 00:29:24,700
One, two, three!

670
00:29:25,130 --> 00:29:27,470
One, two, three!

671
00:29:28,610 --> 00:29:29,060
Come on!

672
00:29:29,060 --> 00:29:31,120
One, two, three!

673
00:29:31,500 --> 00:29:31,960
Come on!

674
00:29:54,300 --> 00:29:55,020
How is it?

675
00:29:55,700 --> 00:29:57,430
Looks like a fuel line problem.

676
00:29:57,640 --> 00:29:58,840
Then that's serious.

677
00:29:59,890 --> 00:30:00,880
Did you bring spare parts?

678
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:01,380
Yes.

679
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:05,330
Captain,

680
00:30:05,820 --> 00:30:06,970
you go on ahead with them later.

681
00:30:06,970 --> 00:30:08,570
I'll fix the car and catch up.

682
00:30:11,810 --> 00:30:12,670
Leave it there.

683
00:30:12,940 --> 00:30:13,790
You guys go first.

684
00:30:13,790 --> 00:30:14,490
We can't split up.

685
00:30:14,490 --> 00:30:15,480
It's too dangerous.

686
00:30:15,480 --> 00:30:16,370
We can't wait.

687
00:30:17,160 --> 00:30:18,040
We're already

688
00:30:18,070 --> 00:30:19,200
an hour behind them.

689
00:30:19,550 --> 00:30:20,570
If it starts raining

690
00:30:20,570 --> 00:30:21,370
and the tire tracks disappear,

691
00:30:21,370 --> 00:30:23,300
it'll be even harder to chase them.

692
00:30:24,180 --> 00:30:24,880
Still no.

693
00:30:25,790 --> 00:30:26,840
You help her fix the car.

694
00:30:26,840 --> 00:30:27,420
You three,

695
00:30:27,420 --> 00:30:28,420
start a fire and make some noodles.

696
00:30:28,420 --> 00:30:28,900
Okay.

697
00:30:28,920 --> 00:30:29,850
Let's rest here.

698
00:30:29,850 --> 00:30:30,290
Okay.

699
00:30:38,140 --> 00:30:38,720
Should I...

700
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,720
Just go help them.

701
00:30:39,740 --> 00:30:40,240
Okay.

702
00:30:40,840 --> 00:30:41,220
Go.

703
00:30:41,240 --> 00:30:41,570
Okay.

704
00:31:08,930 --> 00:31:09,790
Move over a bit.

705
00:31:15,530 --> 00:31:16,490
Captain, take a break.

706
00:31:16,490 --> 00:31:17,440
Have some noodles.

707
00:31:17,440 --> 00:31:17,870
Okay.

708
00:31:19,570 --> 00:31:20,100
It's hot.

709
00:31:25,250 --> 00:31:25,870
Take a break.

710
00:31:25,870 --> 00:31:26,840
Have some noodles.

711
00:31:26,840 --> 00:31:27,470
I'm not hungry.

712
00:31:27,470 --> 00:31:28,600
Give it to Han first.

713
00:31:30,940 --> 00:31:31,290
Here.

714
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:32,030
Okay.

715
00:31:40,040 --> 00:31:40,670
Captain,

716
00:31:40,920 --> 00:31:41,730
you try it.

717
00:31:54,250 --> 00:31:54,910
It's fixed!

718
00:31:55,070 --> 00:31:55,600
Let's go!

719
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:56,850
Bravo!

720
00:32:06,360 --> 00:32:08,090
Why are you smiling so goofily?

721
00:32:08,340 --> 00:32:09,050
Why is my girlfriend

722
00:32:09,050 --> 00:32:10,330
so cool?

723
00:32:13,040 --> 00:32:13,940
Get moving.

724
00:32:37,400 --> 00:32:38,050
Oh no.

725
00:32:42,650 --> 00:32:43,240
What's that bright thing

726
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,170
in the distance?

727
00:32:56,270 --> 00:32:57,330
Something's wrong.

728
00:32:57,330 --> 00:32:58,090
How...

729
00:32:58,370 --> 00:32:59,970
How can there be a river here?

730
00:33:00,500 --> 00:33:01,830
It snowed a few days ago.

731
00:33:02,660 --> 00:33:03,920
The sun's been strong.

732
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:05,430
The meltwater from the mountains
rushed down

733
00:33:05,430 --> 00:33:06,690
and carved out a river.

734
00:33:07,010 --> 00:33:08,340
I told you to go on ahead.

735
00:33:09,940 --> 00:33:10,850
Don't you know

736
00:33:10,880 --> 00:33:11,840
what Bolamula is like

737
00:33:11,840 --> 00:33:12,900
in summer?

738
00:33:13,480 --> 00:33:14,260
They had just driven through

739
00:33:14,260 --> 00:33:14,930
not long ago

740
00:33:15,010 --> 00:33:16,240
when the water came down.

741
00:33:16,240 --> 00:33:18,900
Could it be the Mountain God
is protecting them?

742
00:33:19,300 --> 00:33:20,770
Can you just shut up?

743
00:33:21,610 --> 00:33:22,270
It's fine.

744
00:33:22,550 --> 00:33:22,980
It's fine.

745
00:33:22,980 --> 00:33:24,510
We've chased them this far.

746
00:33:24,510 --> 00:33:25,370
There has to be another way

747
00:33:25,370 --> 00:33:26,830
to figure out their route.

748
00:33:28,040 --> 00:33:29,100
I'll drive across.

749
00:33:29,310 --> 00:33:30,960
I've done it before!

750
00:33:31,460 --> 00:33:32,080
No!

751
00:33:32,590 --> 00:33:33,270
It's different this time!

752
00:33:33,270 --> 00:33:33,900
If you get stuck,

753
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:35,110
we won't have time to pull you out.

754
00:33:35,110 --> 00:33:35,720
Stop!

755
00:33:38,110 --> 00:33:39,160
We'll detour and try to catch up.

756
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:40,270
Okay.

757
00:33:40,630 --> 00:33:41,160
Let's go.

758
00:33:58,640 --> 00:34:01,170
Tomorrow we'll have to
cross a mountain pass.

759
00:34:01,480 --> 00:34:02,180
The altitude will be higher

760
00:34:02,180 --> 00:34:03,440
and the wind stronger.

761
00:34:03,680 --> 00:34:04,610
The tire tracks

762
00:34:04,640 --> 00:34:05,330
they leave

763
00:34:06,140 --> 00:34:06,980
may disappear

764
00:34:07,010 --> 00:34:08,050
in just a few hours.

765
00:34:08,050 --> 00:34:09,650
That's not the only problem.

766
00:34:10,570 --> 00:34:12,860
At higher altitude,
fuel consumption shoots up.

767
00:34:12,860 --> 00:34:14,590
Engine power will be affected,

768
00:34:14,870 --> 00:34:16,670
and we won't have enough torque.

769
00:34:16,679 --> 00:34:17,360
I'm afraid

770
00:34:18,340 --> 00:34:19,110
the gap between us

771
00:34:19,110 --> 00:34:20,050
will only grow.

772
00:34:21,300 --> 00:34:22,449
If there's no road,

773
00:34:22,800 --> 00:34:23,730
then we don't go.

774
00:34:25,260 --> 00:34:27,040
We turn back and do regular patrols.

775
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,420
Next time they go into the mountains,

776
00:34:28,420 --> 00:34:29,630
we'll follow them in a different way.

777
00:34:29,630 --> 00:34:30,710
If there were a better way,

778
00:34:30,710 --> 00:34:31,960
we would've thought of it already.

779
00:34:31,960 --> 00:34:33,889
We wouldn't have waited until now.

780
00:34:34,719 --> 00:34:36,179
Next time, we'll only face

781
00:34:37,300 --> 00:34:39,300
the same difficulties as this time.

782
00:34:41,400 --> 00:34:42,150
If you ask me,

783
00:34:43,050 --> 00:34:45,050
we've been in here for almost 2 days.

784
00:34:45,360 --> 00:34:46,370
We can't be far

785
00:34:46,400 --> 00:34:47,760
from their destination.

786
00:34:47,760 --> 00:34:48,420
Why don't we

787
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,100
try to estimate their direction

788
00:34:51,100 --> 00:34:52,100
and keep chasing?

789
00:34:53,710 --> 00:34:54,570
Give me the map.

790
00:35:01,000 --> 00:35:01,760
This is the place

791
00:35:01,760 --> 00:35:04,160
where Zhang Yang was caught
the first time.

792
00:35:05,380 --> 00:35:06,940
This is where Zhang Yang and Tashi

793
00:35:06,940 --> 00:35:08,200
were caught together.

794
00:35:10,380 --> 00:35:10,840
And here

795
00:35:11,350 --> 00:35:12,280
is where we rescued them

796
00:35:12,280 --> 00:35:13,010
by the river.

797
00:35:13,860 --> 00:35:15,900
The three locations are far apart,

798
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:20,170
each near a large river.

799
00:35:20,770 --> 00:35:22,410
If we follow the rivers,

800
00:35:23,450 --> 00:35:26,110
they lead to
completely different directions.

801
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:28,930
Let's split into teams and search.

802
00:35:30,440 --> 00:35:31,300
Not a good idea.

803
00:35:31,650 --> 00:35:32,470
Even if we find them,

804
00:35:32,470 --> 00:35:34,600
we won't be able to contact each other.

805
00:35:34,710 --> 00:35:35,570
It's too risky.

806
00:35:38,930 --> 00:35:40,330
This is the map Dolma used

807
00:35:40,430 --> 00:35:41,610
with her classmates when they

808
00:35:41,610 --> 00:35:43,010
went into the mountains.

809
00:35:44,190 --> 00:35:45,850
They marked all the gold belts

810
00:35:46,190 --> 00:35:47,180
they found

811
00:35:47,210 --> 00:35:48,050
and any that

812
00:35:48,340 --> 00:35:49,590
might exist.

813
00:35:51,000 --> 00:35:52,010
There are some differences

814
00:35:52,010 --> 00:35:52,880
from the gold spots along the river

815
00:35:52,880 --> 00:35:54,210
where fossickers work.

816
00:35:54,840 --> 00:35:55,730
We can see if there are

817
00:35:55,730 --> 00:35:56,860
any possibilities.

818
00:35:58,320 --> 00:35:59,580
Where are we right now?

819
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:00,990
Around...

820
00:36:02,300 --> 00:36:02,900
here.

821
00:36:03,010 --> 00:36:03,800
The two gold belts

822
00:36:03,800 --> 00:36:04,690
closest to us

823
00:36:05,030 --> 00:36:06,230
are Duolong Mountain

824
00:36:07,710 --> 00:36:08,510
and...

825
00:36:09,150 --> 00:36:10,130
Mount Qimar.

826
00:36:13,770 --> 00:36:14,830
One is to the north,

827
00:36:15,730 --> 00:36:17,330
and the other is to the south.

828
00:36:18,020 --> 00:36:19,710
Two completely different directions.

829
00:36:19,710 --> 00:36:20,770
If we choose wrong,

830
00:36:22,930 --> 00:36:24,530
we'll definitely lose them.

831
00:36:39,510 --> 00:36:40,070
Bai Ju,

832
00:36:40,750 --> 00:36:41,880
what's your choice?

833
00:36:48,700 --> 00:36:50,630
When we saved Zhang Yang and Tashi,

834
00:36:51,660 --> 00:36:53,320
we confiscated their trucks.

835
00:36:55,670 --> 00:36:57,270
How much gas did we find in it?

836
00:37:01,590 --> 00:37:02,390
Sixty liters.

837
00:37:03,130 --> 00:37:04,030
Sixty liters...

838
00:37:04,030 --> 00:37:05,690
plus what was left in the tank.

839
00:37:07,090 --> 00:37:07,880
With one large

840
00:37:07,880 --> 00:37:09,010
and one small truck,

841
00:37:10,340 --> 00:37:11,020
their range

842
00:37:11,050 --> 00:37:12,850
wouldn't exceed 90 kilometers.

843
00:37:15,360 --> 00:37:16,420
One to one million.

844
00:37:16,860 --> 00:37:17,800
90 kilometers

845
00:37:18,830 --> 00:37:19,830
is 9 centimeters.

846
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:21,360
He Qingyuan,

847
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:22,390
give me a piece of string.

848
00:37:22,390 --> 00:37:23,120
Will this do?

849
00:37:23,530 --> 00:37:24,090
Yes.

850
00:37:45,690 --> 00:37:47,990
[Mount Qimar]

851
00:37:54,910 --> 00:37:56,240
Let's go to Mount Qimar.

852
00:38:14,470 --> 00:38:15,170
Don't rush.

853
00:38:16,210 --> 00:38:17,010
Drive slowly.

854
00:38:18,050 --> 00:38:18,630
Okay.

855
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:03,800
Drive slowly.

856
00:39:07,030 --> 00:39:08,290
There's a reflection!

857
00:39:09,000 --> 00:39:09,810
One o'clock!

858
00:39:10,160 --> 00:39:11,150
Drive over there.

859
00:39:11,150 --> 00:39:11,650
Okay.

860
00:39:27,690 --> 00:39:28,590
It's wood.

861
00:39:28,930 --> 00:39:29,790
It must be them.

862
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:32,640
It's the reflection from a tin can.

863
00:39:33,130 --> 00:39:34,320
Bastards!

864
00:39:35,260 --> 00:39:36,050
Captain!

865
00:39:36,420 --> 00:39:37,950
There are tire tracks here!

866
00:41:42,030 --> 00:41:42,630
Got it?

867
00:41:42,650 --> 00:41:43,290
Got it.

868
00:42:12,510 --> 00:42:14,050
They opened a door?

869
00:42:14,830 --> 00:42:15,510
Is there something

870
00:42:15,510 --> 00:42:17,040
between the wooden stakes?

871
00:42:17,320 --> 00:42:18,050
Barbed wire.

872
00:42:19,500 --> 00:42:20,830
It's almost invisible.

873
00:42:21,180 --> 00:42:21,900
You wouldn't notice it

874
00:42:21,900 --> 00:42:23,100
unless you get close.

875
00:42:23,200 --> 00:42:24,210
And this area isn't part

876
00:42:24,210 --> 00:42:26,210
of the Tibetan antelope's habitat.

877
00:42:26,440 --> 00:42:28,440
We've never patrolled here before.

878
00:42:30,860 --> 00:42:32,920
We'll need to expand our patrol zones

879
00:42:33,090 --> 00:42:34,210
in the future.

880
00:42:36,140 --> 00:42:37,070
Look over there.

881
00:42:42,800 --> 00:42:43,510
It looks like

882
00:42:43,510 --> 00:42:44,710
a dried-up riverbed.

883
00:42:45,040 --> 00:42:46,500
It's very clear on the map.

884
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:48,580
Look.

885
00:42:50,190 --> 00:42:51,570
Where does the Manri River

886
00:42:51,570 --> 00:42:52,340
lead?

887
00:42:53,420 --> 00:42:54,750
Manri River

888
00:42:56,260 --> 00:42:57,520
flows from west to east

889
00:42:57,590 --> 00:42:58,650
and runs all the way

890
00:42:58,940 --> 00:43:00,070
through

891
